Sunian.

36
00:02:18,470 --> 00:02:20,490
Zhang Qi.

37
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:25,150
Shadow Clone Technique! <i>(From the Japanese manga, "Naruto")</i>

38
00:02:30,660 --> 00:02:36,560
Are you really not going to consider joining my stage play?

39
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:38,980
I've told you.

40
00:02:38,980 --> 00:02:40,513
I'm not in.

41
00:02:40,513 --> 00:02:41,860
I have to go dancing.

42
00:02:41,860 --> 00:02:44,560
I might drag the progression as I don't have much time.

43
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:46,860
Perhaps I can help with the props?

44
00:02:46,860 --> 00:02:50,570
Please help me.

45
00:02:50,570 --> 00:02:53,810
I just want to be a director for once. Can't you help me?

46
00:03:04,460 --> 00:03:08,600
So it doesn't work when I ask you politely or when I act cute, huh?

47
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:10,293
Okay.

48
00:03:10,293 --> 00:03:13,940
In that case, are you forcing me to use...

49
00:03:13,940 --> 00:03:15,550
- No way.
- My birthday privilege?

50
00:03:15,550 --> 00:03:17,240
No, please.

51
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:18,680
My birthday falls on the day of the school's anniversary.

52
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:21,560
You've promised me that you'd fulfill any of my birthday wishes.

53
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:24,630
I want you to help me deliver a marvelous stage play.

54
00:03:25,470 --> 00:03:27,103
Well.

55
00:03:27,103 --> 00:03:30,500
Three gentlemen are here,

56
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:34,350
which of you is going to be my male lead?

57
00:03:36,610 --> 00:03:39,210
I can't even fit in the costume.

58
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:44,130
It must be Sunian.

59
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:46,300
But I don't wish to.

60
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:49,180
Anyway, Sunian is in the Prince Ranking.

61
00:03:49,180 --> 00:03:50,413
What?

62
00:03:50,413 --> 00:03:54,430
Prince Ranking. The ranking for school hunks.

63
00:03:54,430 --> 00:03:56,340
You're not in.

64
00:03:56,340 --> 00:03:58,030
Sunian has been in the top ten.

65
00:03:58,030 --> 00:03:59,810
What nonsense is this?

66
00:03:59,810 --> 00:04:02,900
It does exist though. There's a Princess Ranking as well.

67
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:07,450
Lin Shiyin. Top one of this month.

68
00:04:07,450 --> 00:04:10,360
This is not credible at all.

69
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:13,000
Who'll be the female lead?

70
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:14,200
Is it her?

71
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:18,490
Unfortunately, I'm too popular. I'm preoccupied.

72
00:04:18,490 --> 00:04:21,193
Not her. It's Tang Ya.

73
00:04:21,193 --> 00:04:22,560
Who is it?

74
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:24,820
My new deskmate.

75
00:04:25,490 --> 00:04:27,390
She's a bit nervous.

76
00:04:27,390 --> 00:04:30,160
But it's fine. I'll handle it.

77
00:04:30,160 --> 00:04:31,800
I've got other plans so I'll leave now.

78
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:33,980
- I'll walk you there.
- No need.

79
00:04:35,390 --> 00:04:37,380
Just leave her alone.

80
00:04:37,380 --> 00:04:41,530
Well. Let's designate the characters now.

81
00:04:42,060 --> 00:04:44,360
You play as the protagonist. You'll be the antagonist.

82
00:04:44,390 --> 00:04:45,930
Then... I want to play as a good person.

83
00:04:45,930 --> 00:04:47,650
You don't fit it.

84
00:04:47,650 --> 00:04:50,170
You'll be outstanding if you play it well.

85
00:04:50,170 --> 00:04:51,840
Any example?

86
00:04:51,840 --> 00:04:53,233
For example,

87
00:04:53,233 --> 00:04:55,240
Granny Rong in My Fair Princess.

88
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:57,460
You know it. She's so popular.

89
00:04:57,460 --> 00:04:59,660
Her performance was impeccable.

90
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:03,890
All right now. Let's discuss the screenplay.

91
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:09,750
Once upon a time, there was a beautiful princess.

92
00:05:09,750 --> 00:05:11,940
She was seriously ill.

93
00:05:11,940 --> 00:05:16,490
There were two warriors who admired the princess which is you and you.

94
00:05:26,530 --> 00:05:27,463
Mr. Luo.

95
00:05:27,463 --> 00:05:28,900
You're here.

96
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:31,490
There's a color that we can't restore.

97
00:05:31,490 --> 00:05:33,400
Could you please take a look?

98
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:35,770
Sure. I'll do it now.

99
00:05:39,270 --> 00:05:43,090
Well. I have something on and I can't go now.

100
00:05:43,090 --> 00:05:45,540
Can you help him, Jin Ning?

101
00:05:46,510 --> 00:05:48,343
Me?

102
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:54,080
You don't want to do me the favor?

103
00:05:54,620 --> 00:05:55,800
That's not what I meant.

104
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:57,920
Perhaps you can do your work first.

105
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:59,480
There's no rush. It's fine to do it later.

106
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:01,013
Wait.

107
00:06:01,013 --> 00:06:04,160
Are you really asking for our help or are you joking around with us?

108
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:05,993
That's right.

109
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:11,720
Hurry up.

110
00:06:27,040 --> 00:06:29,000
The savior is finally here.

111
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:31,970
Madam Jin, please take a look at it.

112
00:06:31,970 --> 00:06:35,830
We simply couldn't get this color right.

113
00:06:35,830 --> 00:06:38,080
Let me try it.

114
00:06:38,080 --> 00:06:40,020
It's about the shine.

115
00:06:40,020 --> 00:06:43,100
Can you get the color by just mixing them?

116
00:07:33,220 --> 00:07:34,970
That's about right, isn't it?

117
00:07:34,970 --> 00:07:37,270
I guess so. Let me compare the colors.

118
00:07:37,270 --> 00:07:38,903
Yes.

119
00:07:45,270 --> 00:07:47,090
It works.

120
00:07:47,090 --> 00:07:48,750
The ratio wasn't right.

121
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:50,120
But you can get the color eventually.

122
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:51,360
It's all about trial and error.

123
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:53,510
You're indeed a professional.

124
00:07:53,510 --> 00:07:55,380
You should have asked Tianbao instead.

125
00:07:55,380 --> 00:07:57,430
The Lacquerware Division is better at this.

126
00:07:57,430 --> 00:07:58,610
They are busy finishing a project.

127
00:07:58,610 --> 00:08:01,340
They're slammed.

128
00:08:01,340 --> 00:08:04,620
Well. We'll try it based on the ratio you showed us.

129
00:08:04,620 --> 00:08:05,870
Thank you so much.

130
00:08:05,870 --> 00:08:07,490
It's fine.

131
00:08:07,490 --> 00:08:08,800
I'll take my leave if there's nothing else.

132
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:10,433
Hold on.

133
00:08:10,433 --> 00:08:11,723
Zheng.

134
00:08:11,723 --> 00:08:14,260
Walk Madam Jin back.

135
00:08:15,630 --> 00:08:17,463
Please don't.

136
00:08:20,090 --> 00:08:21,270
Thank you.

137
00:08:21,270 --> 00:08:23,170
<i>No big deal.</i>

138
00:08:23,700 --> 00:08:26,000
- See how she is.
- Walk her back.

139
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:28,270
It's only two steps to the house.

140
00:08:28,270 --> 00:08:30,920
I'll watch her go back.

141
00:08:34,420 --> 00:08:36,153
Okay.

142
00:08:36,153 --> 00:08:38,180
I've watched her going back in.

143
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:42,030
How did you manage to woo her back then?

144
00:08:42,030 --> 00:08:44,570
Mind your own business. Come on, look at this.

145
00:08:45,450 --> 00:08:47,250
Wu Huan, I knew you were the reliable one.

146
00:08:47,250 --> 00:08:48,750
<i>[Activity Room]</i>
You're much more helpful.

147
00:08:48,750 --> 00:08:50,890
They'll come shortly as well.

148
00:08:50,890 --> 00:08:52,510
Have you confirmed the time for your part-time job yet?

149
00:08:52,510 --> 00:08:54,030
Yes. I can make it.

150
00:08:54,030 --> 00:08:56,790
That's great. I have prepared a character that suits you very well.

151
00:08:56,790 --> 00:08:57,840
- Really?
- Yes.

152
00:08:57,840 --> 00:09:04,000
<i>♪ What a beautiful jasmine ♪</i>

153
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:07,480
It sounds familiar.

154
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:13,240
<i>♪ Buds and blooms are here and there ♪</i>

155
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:18,050
<i>♪ Pure and fragrant all do declare ♪</i>

156
00:09:18,050 --> 00:09:22,440
<i>♪ Let me gather some with tender care ♪</i>

157
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:25,290
Tang Ya! You sing so well.

158
00:09:25,290 --> 00:09:27,480
<i>[With melodious music]</i>

159
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:31,990
Do you guys really think it's nice?

160
00:09:31,990 --> 00:09:34,660
It's not about what I think. It's a fact. Am I right, Wu Huan?

161
00:09:34,660 --> 00:09:35,600
It's nice.

162
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:37,910
I've decided to let you be the female lead.

163
00:09:37,910 --> 00:09:39,390
I'll add a solo for you.

164
00:09:39,390 --> 00:09:40,650
Please don't.

165
00:09:40,650 --> 00:09:43,880
I can't sing in front of people.

166
00:09:43,880 --> 00:09:46,403
It's embarrassing.

167
00:09:46,403 --> 00:09:48,620
We'll be by your side.

168
00:09:49,670 --> 00:09:52,120
But I don't think I can do it.

169
00:09:52,120 --> 00:09:55,453
Although it's something I long for, I do feel

170
00:09:55,453 --> 00:09:57,950
quite intimidated.

171
00:09:57,950 --> 00:10:00,820
If there's something that you wish to do, you should go for it.

172
00:10:00,820 --> 00:10:04,130
Not everyone has this opportunity.

173
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:13,240
Then...

174
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:16,820
I'll try.

175
00:10:16,820 --> 00:10:17,790
Great!

176
00:10:17,790 --> 00:10:21,460
Since you sang Jasmine Flower so well, you'll be Princess Jasmine.

177
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:25,890
Can you sing for us again?

178
00:10:25,890 --> 00:10:27,673
Sure.

179
00:10:29,270 --> 00:10:31,720
<i>[Dancing Classroom, Qiming High School]
Five, six, seven, eight.</i>

180
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:35,900
Three, two, three, four, five, six, seven, eight.
<i>[Dance in youth's rhythm, let brilliance bloom]</i>

181
00:10:35,900 --> 00:10:40,240
- Four, two, three, four, five, six, seven, eight.
- Stop.

182
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:42,233
- Five.
- Stop!

183
00:10:46,340 --> 00:10:48,783
What is wrong with you?

184
00:10:50,890 --> 00:10:53,190
Did you listen to the music?

185
00:10:54,130 --> 00:10:55,563
Yes.

186
00:10:55,563 --> 00:10:59,180
Then, can't you feel it?

187
00:10:59,910 --> 00:11:04,370
Can't you feel the misery of death

188
00:11:05,870 --> 00:11:10,663
and the despair as the end of the world is coming?

189
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:14,750
Did you feel them?

190
00:11:14,750 --> 00:11:16,940
Then, how could you dance so badly?

191
00:11:18,410 --> 00:11:21,870
I saw no despair in you.

192
00:11:21,870 --> 00:11:26,260
I could even see that you were happy.

193
00:11:29,630 --> 00:11:32,170
I've tried my best, sir.

194
00:11:33,340 --> 00:11:37,120
Sorry. I'm too strict.

195
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:41,353
I think it's because of your temperament.

196
00:11:41,353 --> 00:11:43,480
You don't fit this dance.

197
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:45,930
I want to change the lead dancer.

198
00:11:45,930 --> 00:11:48,410
Mr. Nai, we're running out of time.

199
00:11:48,410 --> 00:11:52,200
It is the art that I'm trying to create here, not a laughingstock.

200
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:54,550
I'll take the responsibility, okay?

201
00:11:54,550 --> 00:11:56,430
Change her position.

202
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:06,140
<i>[Dance in youth's rhythm, let brilliance bloom]</i>

203
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:24,240
What is your name?

204
00:12:25,030 --> 00:12:26,963
Lin Shiyin.

205
00:12:27,790 --> 00:12:29,740
Do you like martial heroes?

206
00:12:29,740 --> 00:12:31,200
I do.

207
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:33,500
Come forward.

208
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:37,000
Repeat her moves.

209
00:12:46,380 --> 00:12:48,530
It's too exaggerated.

210
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,800
But it's better than hers.

211
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:55,970
You'll be the lead dancer.

212
00:12:55,970 --> 00:12:57,500
Come on, let's continue.

213
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:59,440
Let's continue in a circle.

214
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:03,240
Come on. Five, six, seven, eight, three, two.

215
00:13:03,300 --> 00:13:07,000
Ms. Yu, I won't ask for more. Just make me look dashing.

216
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:09,150
You don't need my help with that.

217
00:13:09,150 --> 00:13:10,440
You are quite handsome already.

218
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:13,630
Mom, why did you lie through your teeth?

219
00:13:13,630 --> 00:13:16,510
Why do you always stop her from saying the truth?

220
00:13:17,790 --> 00:13:20,250
Next in line.

221
00:13:20,250 --> 00:13:22,873
Ms. Yu, it'll be a waste to make a costume for me.

222
00:13:22,873 --> 00:13:25,210
Maybe you can just leave mine out.

223
00:13:25,210 --> 00:13:27,740
The costumes must be in full sets.

224
00:13:27,740 --> 00:13:29,810
Mom, you're so cooperative this time.

225
00:13:29,810 --> 00:13:32,530
Is it because you've realized my talent?

226
00:13:32,530 --> 00:13:34,410
Dream on.

227
00:13:34,410 --> 00:13:38,210
When I was young, I participated in a play, too.

228
00:13:38,210 --> 00:13:41,340
However, I couldn't make it as something cropped up.

229
00:13:41,340 --> 00:13:42,720
Take it seriously.

230
00:13:42,720 --> 00:13:44,340
Help me fulfill my dream.

231
00:13:44,340 --> 00:13:47,090
You can count on me, Mom.

232
00:13:47,090 --> 00:13:50,041
Ms. Yu, I have to work now.

233
00:13:50,041 --> 00:13:52,010
See you, Ms. Yu. Bye-bye.

234
00:13:52,010 --> 00:13:54,051
Remember to practice.

235
00:13:54,740 --> 00:13:56,910
Come, Sunian.

236
00:13:58,340 --> 00:14:00,180
Look at Sunian.

237
00:14:00,180 --> 00:14:02,140
He has such a good build.

238
00:14:02,140 --> 00:14:04,000
Likes a model's figure.

239
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:06,300
You're indeed my great male lead.

240
00:14:06,300 --> 00:14:09,780
Ms. Yu, don't I have a good build as well?

241
00:14:11,070 --> 00:14:15,440
Brat, I'm just saying that every one of you has your own strengths.

242
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:18,030
Why did you have to embarrass yourself?

243
00:14:18,030 --> 00:14:20,580
Mind your own business.

244
00:14:20,580 --> 00:14:23,970
Mom, it's the body measurement of the female lead.

245
00:14:23,970 --> 00:14:27,913
Sure. I'll handle the costumes.

246
00:14:27,913 --> 00:14:29,433
It's done.

247
00:14:32,250 --> 00:14:35,140
Sunian, where's your mother?

248
00:14:35,140 --> 00:14:37,350
She went to the Restoration Department.

249
00:14:38,980 --> 00:14:43,060
Why did she go there on the weekend?

250
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:54,300
They haven't reconciled?

251
00:14:57,650 --> 00:14:59,300
Where's your dad?

252
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:01,260
He went there, too.

253
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:02,920
Oh my, this couple.

254
00:15:02,920 --> 00:15:05,821
Sunian, did your parents have a squabble?

255
00:15:07,700 --> 00:15:08,860
Why don't we join them?

256
00:15:08,860 --> 00:15:10,193
What for?

257
00:15:10,193 --> 00:15:11,950
To give a helping hand to Mr. Zheng.

258
00:15:11,950 --> 00:15:13,410
Don't make it worse.

259
00:15:13,410 --> 00:15:15,241
I won't. Let's go.

260
00:15:15,241 --> 00:15:16,733
See you, Mom.

261
00:15:16,733 --> 00:15:18,440
I'll get going now, Ms. Yu.

262
00:15:18,440 --> 00:15:19,950
- Goodbye, Ms. Yu.
- Bye, Mom.

263
00:15:19,950 --> 00:15:21,933
Bye-bye.

264
00:15:25,870 --> 00:15:28,420
<i>[Shi Zu Store]</i>

265
00:15:37,220 --> 00:15:39,390
How may I help you?

266
00:15:43,220 --> 00:15:45,253
Wu Huan.

267
00:15:45,253 --> 00:15:46,620
Tang Ya.

268
00:15:46,620 --> 00:15:49,920
What a coincidence. Are you working here?

269
00:15:49,920 --> 00:15:52,330
I'm here every weekend.

270
00:15:52,330 --> 00:15:55,130
What do you want? I'll get it for you.

271
00:15:55,130 --> 00:15:56,473
No need.

272
00:15:57,050 --> 00:15:59,380
Continue with your work. I'll just browse by myself.

273
00:15:59,380 --> 00:16:00,980
Sure.

274
00:16:12,630 --> 00:16:17,663
Wu Huan, is the shop still hiring?

275
00:16:17,663 --> 00:16:19,600
I want a part-time job too.

276
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:22,190
How's your rehearsal going?

277
00:16:22,190 --> 00:16:25,555
Sunian, show me how you growl because of anger.

278
00:16:30,055 --> 00:16:32,625
That was perfunctory.

279
00:16:33,765 --> 00:16:35,515
You give it a go.

280
00:16:38,885 --> 00:16:40,886
I want you to growl not bark.

281
00:16:40,886 --> 00:16:44,715
You two didn't practice at all.

282
00:16:45,815 --> 00:16:47,948
Mr. Luo.

283
00:16:47,948 --> 00:16:50,885
I always bump into you every time I come here.

284
00:16:50,885 --> 00:16:53,045
Look at what you've said.

285
00:16:53,045 --> 00:16:54,885
I've been working here for forty years.

286
00:16:54,885 --> 00:16:56,635
Isn't it the weekend?

287
00:16:56,635 --> 00:16:58,145
I have nothing to do staying at home alone.

288
00:16:58,145 --> 00:17:00,045
It's better to come here to work.

289
00:17:00,045 --> 00:17:01,595
What brings you here?

290
00:17:01,595 --> 00:17:03,655
I want to ask Ms. Jin Ning to draw something for me.

291
00:17:03,655 --> 00:17:05,825
She's inside. Off you go.

292
00:17:09,155 --> 00:17:11,405
She's not in a good mood.

293
00:17:25,565 --> 00:17:27,415
Does it taste good?

294
00:17:27,415 --> 00:17:29,398
Have some more.

295
00:17:48,955 --> 00:17:51,555
Is Ms. Jin Ning still upset?

296
00:17:52,475 --> 00:17:55,025
There's tension in the air.

297
00:17:57,185 --> 00:17:59,635
It makes me feel like I'm home now.

298
00:18:01,615 --> 00:18:03,348
Xue.

299
00:18:03,348 --> 00:18:05,745
- Ms. Jin Ning.
- Ms. Jin Ning.

300
00:18:05,745 --> 00:18:07,045
What brings you here?

301
00:18:07,045 --> 00:18:08,605
Ms. Jin Ning.

302
00:18:08,605 --> 00:18:09,775
Mr. Zheng.

303
00:18:09,775 --> 00:18:12,075
Come in and have a seat.

304
00:18:12,905 --> 00:18:14,638
Come on.

305
00:18:15,615 --> 00:18:17,448
Sunian.

306
00:18:21,575 --> 00:18:22,908
It's for you.

307
00:18:22,908 --> 00:18:24,758
Thank you.

308
00:18:24,758 --> 00:18:26,465
The manager said we are still hiring.

309
00:18:26,465 --> 00:18:28,905
But he's busy now. He'll talk to you later.

310
00:18:28,905 --> 00:18:31,525
I think he'll agree.

311
00:18:31,525 --> 00:18:34,105
- Thank you so much.
- No big deal.

312
00:18:36,185 --> 00:18:40,195
By the way, why do you need a part-time job?

313
00:18:42,645 --> 00:18:48,578
I... just want to earn money and buy something I want.

314
00:18:50,855 --> 00:18:54,315
Ms. Yu is making new costumes for us.

315
00:18:54,315 --> 00:18:58,125
She's an expert at it. The costumes will be awesome.

316
00:18:58,125 --> 00:19:01,676
I'm kind of looking forward to your singing on stage.

317
00:19:03,715 --> 00:19:07,648
Hopefully, I won't screw up the show.

318
00:19:09,135 --> 00:19:10,615
To the success of our performance.

319
00:19:10,615 --> 00:19:12,348
Cheers.

320
00:19:12,925 --> 00:19:15,025
To the success of our performance.

321
00:19:38,375 --> 00:19:42,545
We have Ms. Yu making the costumes and Ms. Jin Ning drawing the props.

322
00:19:42,545 --> 00:19:44,645
Your play might be mediocre, but the preparation is quite something.

323
00:19:44,645 --> 00:19:45,845
Well, we need to do our best regardless of the result.

324
00:19:45,845 --> 00:19:47,595
Are you admitting defeat before the show starts?

325
00:19:47,595 --> 00:19:48,805
Do you want to get kicked out of the show?

326
00:19:48,805 --> 00:19:52,006
I'm just worried that it will be too much trouble for Ms. Jin Ning.

327
00:19:52,855 --> 00:19:54,135
I have no choice though.

328
00:19:54,135 --> 00:19:57,175
Since I have received the cake as payment,

329
00:19:57,175 --> 00:19:59,575
I should do my job well.

330
00:20:01,475 --> 00:20:03,725
Who bought this cake?

331
00:20:03,725 --> 00:20:06,475
This person knows my taste well.

332
00:20:11,135 --> 00:20:14,768
I guess it's Xue, right?

333
00:20:15,325 --> 00:20:19,665
No way. She can do nothing apart from eating.

334
00:20:19,665 --> 00:20:23,445
- Not me.
- It's Sunian. He especially...
- Let's go play with the cat.

335
00:20:25,195 --> 00:20:27,465
My mom prefers a quiet environment.

336
00:20:27,465 --> 00:20:29,365
I don't.

337
00:20:29,365 --> 00:20:31,965
I'm different from you and your dad.

338
00:20:37,265 --> 00:20:38,955
Well. Go out and play.

339
00:20:38,955 --> 00:20:40,375
I'll call you when it's done.

340
00:20:40,375 --> 00:20:42,425
Thank you so much, Ms. Jin Ning.

341
00:20:42,425 --> 00:20:43,855
You're most welcome.

342
00:20:43,855 --> 00:20:46,475
Let's go. Sure.

343
00:20:46,475 --> 00:20:49,305
Mom, don't eat too much sweet food.

344
00:20:50,615 --> 00:20:52,448
Okay.

345
00:21:01,375 --> 00:21:03,095
Mr. Luo.

346
00:21:03,095 --> 00:21:04,405
What are you doing?

347
00:21:04,405 --> 00:21:06,275
Something's wrong with the watering can.

348
00:21:06,275 --> 00:21:08,325
The water doesn't come out.

349
00:21:08,325 --> 00:21:09,675
Let me take a look at it.

350
00:21:09,675 --> 00:21:11,475
You can't handle it.

351
00:21:13,225 --> 00:21:14,920
Zhang Qi.

352
00:21:15,658 --> 00:21:16,685
- What's wrong?
- Fix this.

353
00:21:16,685 --> 00:21:17,905
He can't do it either.

354
00:21:17,905 --> 00:21:19,655
I'll give it a try.

355
00:21:20,545 --> 00:21:22,895
Why did you guys come here this Sunday

356
00:21:22,895 --> 00:21:25,925
instead of hanging out elsewhere?

357
00:21:25,925 --> 00:21:27,985
We are going to prepare for a stage play.

358
00:21:27,985 --> 00:21:30,265
So, we are here to ask for some help from Ms. Jin Ning.

359
00:21:30,265 --> 00:21:32,525
What is it about?

360
00:21:32,525 --> 00:21:34,095
For now, I only have the framework for the screenplay.

361
00:21:34,095 --> 00:21:35,615
Anyway, it's a costume play.

362
00:21:35,615 --> 00:21:38,745
I want to add some fantasy elements to the concept of martial heroes

363
00:21:38,745 --> 00:21:41,455
and comedy elements to the fantasy concept.

364
00:21:41,455 --> 00:21:42,845
I can't understand at all.

365
00:21:42,845 --> 00:21:43,905
How's it going?

366
00:21:43,905 --> 00:21:45,045
Not only you, Mr. Luo.

367
00:21:45,045 --> 00:21:46,585
- We don't get it either.
- All fixed.

368
00:21:46,585 --> 00:21:48,575
I wanted to make it clear.

369
00:21:48,575 --> 00:21:50,055
However, everyone voices their opinions.

370
00:21:50,055 --> 00:21:51,425
And I'm confused about how I am going to fix it.

371
00:21:51,425 --> 00:21:53,185
Someone said it lacks depth.

372
00:21:53,185 --> 00:21:54,805
While the other one said it's not passionate enough.

373
00:21:54,805 --> 00:21:57,815
And when I'm done amending the script, Ms. Jin Ning said

374
00:21:57,815 --> 00:21:59,965
it isn't romantic enough.

375
00:21:59,965 --> 00:22:01,815
She... She... She's right.

376
00:22:01,815 --> 00:22:06,495
I reckon a stage play must be romantic.

377
00:22:06,495 --> 00:22:10,275
Mr. Luo, but I have no idea what romance is about?

378
00:22:10,275 --> 00:22:13,025
Maybe you can tell us a romantic story?

379
00:22:13,025 --> 00:22:14,675
We can learn from it.

380
00:22:14,675 --> 00:22:17,015
I don't know how to tell stories.

381
00:22:17,015 --> 00:22:19,365
Did you forget that you used to tell me stories while carrying me when I was young?

382
00:22:19,365 --> 00:22:21,195
When did I do that?

383
00:22:21,195 --> 00:22:22,535
You did. I've heard it before.

384
00:22:22,535 --> 00:22:24,368
Me too.

385
00:22:25,405 --> 00:22:29,686
Well. Then I'll tell you one today, all right?

386
00:22:29,686 --> 00:22:31,665
Sunian, give me a stool.

387
00:22:37,605 --> 00:22:39,238
Got it.

388
00:22:44,265 --> 00:22:48,225
The story I'm telling happened at this place.

389
00:22:48,225 --> 00:22:49,935
Promise me first.

390
00:22:49,935 --> 00:22:54,095
The characters in this story might be real or fictional.

391
00:22:54,095 --> 00:22:57,006
Don't let your imagination run wild. Okay?

392
00:23:00,185 --> 00:23:01,518
Got it.

393
00:23:02,995 --> 00:23:06,595
This story happened a long time ago.

394
00:23:06,595 --> 00:23:11,605
Back then, at this place, there were two people.

395
00:23:24,765 --> 00:23:26,425
<i>Go away.</i>

396
00:23:26,425 --> 00:23:28,535
<i>Don't just eat whatever you see. Go now.</i>

397
00:23:28,535 --> 00:23:29,885
<i>You are eating random stuff again.</i>

398
00:23:29,885 --> 00:23:31,805
<i>I've told you so many times. Be careful with what you eat.</i>

399
00:23:31,805 --> 00:23:34,465
<i>You... Why did you drive it away?</i>

400
00:23:34,465 --> 00:23:36,375
<i>It's just eating something as it's hungry.</i>

401
00:23:36,375 --> 00:23:37,905
<i>You're so heartless.</i>

402
00:23:37,905 --> 00:23:40,055
<i>So indifferent.</i>

403
00:23:41,465 --> 00:23:43,575
<i>Sorry.</i>

404
00:23:46,845 --> 00:23:48,745
<i>Madam Jin, you've misunderstood Mr. Zheng.</i>

405
00:23:48,745 --> 00:23:50,135
<i>Recently, there have been a lot of rats here.</i>

406
00:23:50,135 --> 00:23:53,515
<i>There is rodenticide there, he's afraid that the kitty might get poisoned.</i>

407
00:24:02,945 --> 00:24:05,165
<i>Kitty, you're injured.</i>

408
00:24:05,165 --> 00:24:08,125
<i>Let me help you treat the wounds. Stay still.</i>

409
00:24:10,775 --> 00:24:13,655
<i>Hey, you're the gentleman from the Watchmaker Division.</i>

410
00:24:13,655 --> 00:24:16,375
<i>Could you please help me?</i>

411
00:24:16,375 --> 00:24:17,925
<i>It's injured.</i>

412
00:24:17,925 --> 00:24:21,025
<i>Could you hold its paws?</i>

413
00:24:21,025 --> 00:24:22,805
<i>I'm going to apply some medicine to it.</i>

414
00:24:22,805 --> 00:24:25,638
<i>But it's a wild cat.</i>

415
00:24:25,638 --> 00:24:27,705
<i>It likes to scratch on people.</i>

416
00:24:27,705 --> 00:24:31,535
<i>But it'll get infected if we don't treat the wounds now.</i>

417
00:24:32,235 --> 00:24:33,325
<i>Thank you.</i>

418
00:24:33,325 --> 00:24:37,325
<i>- Well, I...
- Turn it over.</i>

419
00:24:37,325 --> 00:24:38,325
<i>Sure, no problem.</i>

420
00:24:38,325 --> 00:24:40,505
<i>Thank you.</i>

421
00:24:40,505 --> 00:24:44,505
<i>- Kitty, it might be hurt a little.
-Turn over.</i>

422
00:24:44,505 --> 00:24:46,465
<i>Bear with me.</i>

423
00:24:46,815 --> 00:24:48,865
<i>- Yes.
- Like this?</i>

424
00:24:51,035 --> 00:24:52,568
<i>This...</i>

425
00:24:52,568 --> 00:24:54,565
<i>- It's fine.
- You're hurt.</i>

426
00:24:54,565 --> 00:24:56,435
<i>- It's fine.
- It's my fault.</i>

427
00:24:56,435 --> 00:24:57,915
<i>Sorry.</i>

428
00:24:57,915 --> 00:24:59,805
<i>Let me bring you to the hospital for a jab.</i>

429
00:24:59,805 --> 00:25:02,575
<i>This kitty has scratched us before. I'm fine.</i>

430
00:25:02,575 --> 00:25:05,775
<i>No way. It's my fault. I should take responsibility.</i>

431
00:25:05,775 --> 00:25:08,975
<i>- No need. I... I mean it.
- Let's go.</i>

432
00:25:13,185 --> 00:25:14,885
<i>Honestly, I can go home myself.</i>

433
00:25:14,885 --> 00:25:16,405
<i>I'm fine.</i>

434
00:25:16,405 --> 00:25:19,625
<i>No way. I must send you home.</i>

435
00:25:21,365 --> 00:25:24,005
<i>Just sit quietly.</i>

436
00:25:26,085 --> 00:25:30,945
Since then, these two people have become acquainted.

437
00:25:31,665 --> 00:25:34,975
- Mr. Luo, is it...
- I've told you not to make random guesses.

438
00:25:34,975 --> 00:25:36,535
I see no romance though.

439
00:25:36,535 --> 00:25:38,955
Let him continue.

440
00:25:38,955 --> 00:25:41,945
Once they became acquainted...

441
00:25:53,125 --> 00:25:54,375
<i>Mr. Zheng.</i>

442
00:25:54,375 --> 00:25:55,908
<i>Yes?</i>

443
00:25:56,375 --> 00:25:58,245
<i>Y-Y-You...</i>

444
00:25:58,245 --> 00:25:59,998
<i>You're here.</i>

445
00:26:01,615 --> 00:26:05,105
<i>Thank you for helping me with the cat.</i>

446
00:26:06,775 --> 00:26:08,945
<i>You're welcome.</i>

447
00:26:10,655 --> 00:26:14,535
<i>How's your hand? Has it recovered?</i>

448
00:26:16,125 --> 00:26:17,858
<i>It's fine.</i>

449
00:26:22,705 --> 00:26:24,455
<i>Are you off work now?</i>

450
00:26:25,135 --> 00:26:26,935
<i>What can I do for you?</i>

451
00:26:26,935 --> 00:26:29,085
<i>My music box is broken.</i>

452
00:26:29,085 --> 00:26:30,615
<i>Could you please help me?</i>

453
00:26:30,615 --> 00:26:32,905
<i>Sure, no problem.</i>

454
00:26:51,745 --> 00:26:54,675
<i>This... This isn't something I come across daily.</i>

455
00:26:54,675 --> 00:26:56,565
<i>It's not a local product, right?</i>

456
00:26:56,565 --> 00:26:59,255
<i>It's from overseas.</i>

457
00:27:00,675 --> 00:27:05,625
<i>Actually, I saw you dancing along with the music the other day.</i>

458
00:27:05,625 --> 00:27:07,408
<i>Over...</i>

459
00:27:07,408 --> 00:27:08,705
<i>Over there.</i>

460
00:27:08,705 --> 00:27:11,195
<i>I saw you looking at me.</i>

461
00:27:16,745 --> 00:27:19,605
<i>I heard that you were abroad previously.</i>

462
00:27:19,605 --> 00:27:20,665
<i>Yes.</i>

463
00:27:20,665 --> 00:27:23,675
<i>I studied at an overseas university.</i>

464
00:27:23,675 --> 00:27:28,225
<i>Next year, I'm going to work at an overseas museum.</i>

465
00:27:35,195 --> 00:27:38,340
<i>It's not easy to repair, is it?</i>

466
00:27:38,875 --> 00:27:40,815
<i>No, it's easy.</i>

467
00:27:57,985 --> 00:27:59,418
<i>It's done.</i>

468
00:27:59,418 --> 00:28:01,675
<i>It's done?</i>

469
00:28:01,675 --> 00:28:04,776
<i>Mr. Zheng, you're amazing.</i>

470
00:28:05,405 --> 00:28:06,235
<i>Thank you.</i>

471
00:28:06,235 --> 00:28:08,368
<i>Jin Ning.</i>

472
00:28:08,368 --> 00:28:11,135
<i>You... Do you have to leave?</i>

473
00:28:11,135 --> 00:28:12,325
<i>No, I'm not leaving.</i>

474
00:28:12,325 --> 00:28:14,576
<i>Later, let's have lunch together.</i>

475
00:28:14,576 --> 00:28:16,235
<i>Let me put this back first.</i>

476
00:28:16,235 --> 00:28:18,385
<i>Please wait for me.</i>

477
00:28:24,955 --> 00:28:26,335
<i>Is it confirmed?</i>

478
00:28:26,335 --> 00:28:27,985
<i>You're leaving so soon?</i>

479
00:28:27,985 --> 00:28:29,195
<i>Yes.</i>

480
00:28:29,195 --> 00:28:33,655
<i>The job at the overseas museum has already been arranged.</i>

481
00:28:33,655 --> 00:28:38,025
<i>I wonder when I will see you again after you leave.</i>

482
00:28:38,025 --> 00:28:41,355
<i>Yeah. We've been working together for a long time,</i>

483
00:28:41,355 --> 00:28:43,045
<i>yet you're leaving all of a sudden.</i>

484
00:28:43,045 --> 00:28:44,815
<i>I'll miss you very much.</i>

485
00:28:44,815 --> 00:28:47,885
<i>I will miss you all as well.</i>

486
00:28:50,135 --> 00:28:51,675
<i>When will you be back?</i>

487
00:28:51,675 --> 00:28:53,455
<i>Look at you.</i>

488
00:28:53,455 --> 00:28:55,025
<i>She's leaving soon.</i>

489
00:28:55,025 --> 00:28:56,775
<i>You don't even ask her to stay.</i>

490
00:28:56,775 --> 00:28:58,308
<i>Stupid.</i>

491
00:29:00,645 --> 00:29:02,578
<i>Zhang Jin.</i>

492
00:29:04,945 --> 00:29:08,505
<i>Tomorrow, I'll leave the Restoration Department.</i>

493
00:29:08,600 --> 00:29:13,800
<i>I thought about it for a long time yet I couldn't decide what I should give you as a gift.</i>

494
00:29:13,875 --> 00:29:16,295
<i>I'll give you this music box...</i>

495
00:29:17,425 --> 00:29:20,025
<i>as a souvenir.</i>

496
00:29:28,195 --> 00:29:30,425
<i>Thank you, Jin Ning.</i>

497
00:29:42,095 --> 00:29:47,275
<i>Can you come and see me off tomorrow?</i>

498
00:29:51,705 --> 00:29:53,638
<i>Tomorrow...</i>

499
00:29:54,565 --> 00:29:57,185
<i>I can't see you off tomorrow.</i>

500
00:29:57,925 --> 00:29:59,945
<i>My master...</i>

501
00:30:00,475 --> 00:30:03,165
<i>asked me to finish some work.</i>

502
00:30:06,325 --> 00:30:10,258
<i>I wish you a smooth and safe trip.</i>

503
00:30:44,575 --> 00:30:46,405
<i>Zheng, can I borrow your pliers?</i>

504
00:30:46,405 --> 00:30:48,455
<i>Zheng. Zheng!</i>

505
00:30:48,455 --> 00:30:50,625
<i>Can I borrow your pliers?</i>

506
00:30:55,565 --> 00:30:56,815
<i>Stop drinking.</i>

507
00:30:56,815 --> 00:30:57,905
<i>[Stir Fry Egg Whites, Quick-fried Tripe]</i>

508
00:30:57,905 --> 00:31:01,195
<i>You work so hard during the day and drink so much during the night.</i>

509
00:31:01,195 --> 00:31:03,325
<i>Do you care about your health at all?</i>

510
00:31:03,325 --> 00:31:06,095
<i>Come. I'll drink with you.</i>

511
00:31:15,295 --> 00:31:17,395
<i>Why haven't you had your meal yet?</i>

512
00:31:17,395 --> 00:31:19,528
<i>Mr. Luo, I haven't finished my work.</i>

513
00:31:19,528 --> 00:31:21,598
<i>I'll eat later.</i>

514
00:31:21,598 --> 00:31:24,565
<i>I have a drawing that I just hung on the wall.</i>

515
00:31:24,565 --> 00:31:27,855
<i>Could you help me keep an eye on it? I'm going to eat now.</i>

516
00:31:27,855 --> 00:31:30,495
<i>No, Mr. Luo. Can I do it?</i>

517
00:31:30,495 --> 00:31:33,735
<i>If the paint is dried, I have no idea how to whisk water on it.</i>

518
00:31:33,735 --> 00:31:36,075
<i>You don't have to do that. Just keep an eye on it for me.</i>

519
00:31:36,075 --> 00:31:38,275
<i>I couldn't find anyone else to do it.</i>

520
00:31:38,275 --> 00:31:40,145
<i>My master doesn't allow us...</i>

521
00:31:40,145 --> 00:31:41,645
<i>Just tell me. Can you do it or not?</i>

522
00:31:41,645 --> 00:31:43,278
<i>I can.</i>

523
00:31:44,945 --> 00:31:48,895
<i>Listen... This is the drawing.</i>

524
00:31:48,895 --> 00:31:51,435
<i>Sit on my chair and guard it well.</i>

525
00:31:51,435 --> 00:31:53,375
<i>No, Mr. Luo. I'll just stand here.</i>

526
00:31:53,375 --> 00:31:55,365
<i>- Just sit down.
- Wait.</i>

527
00:31:55,365 --> 00:31:57,465
<i>- I'm worried...
- Nothing to worry about.</i>

528
00:31:57,465 --> 00:31:58,805
<i>Nothing to worry about.</i>

529
00:31:58,805 --> 00:32:01,155
<i>Don't leave until I'm back.</i>

530
00:32:39,985 --> 00:32:46,618
<i>Mr. Luo, you must be annoyed as I've written you so many letters.</i>

531
00:32:46,618 --> 00:32:51,895
<i>However, I'm truly curious about what has happened in the Restoration Department.
[Yours sincerely, Jin Ning]</i>

532
00:32:51,895 --> 00:32:56,415
<i>I'm truly curious about how's he doing recently.</i>

533
00:32:56,945 --> 00:33:00,578
<i>Zheng Jin. How is he recently?</i>

534
00:33:00,578 --> 00:33:04,975
<i>You'd say I was foolish every time I asked this question.</i>

535
00:33:04,975 --> 00:33:09,315
<i>You asked me that since I care for him so much, why did I leave?</i>

536
00:33:09,315 --> 00:33:13,088
<i>Mr. Luo, I've thought about it for a long time</i>

537
00:33:13,088 --> 00:33:15,655
<i>and I've regretted it as well.</i>

538
00:33:15,655 --> 00:33:18,225
<i>Why should I wait for him to confess</i>

539
00:33:18,225 --> 00:33:21,155
<i>and come to look for me?</i>

540
00:33:21,155 --> 00:33:24,775
<i>I should take the initiative and tell him</i>

541
00:33:24,775 --> 00:33:27,715
<i>that I want to stay by his side.</i>

542
00:33:28,315 --> 00:33:32,848
<i>However, I was angry at him back then.</i>

543
00:33:32,848 --> 00:33:36,815
<i>I was angry that why he didn't ask me to stay or look for me.</i>

544
00:33:36,815 --> 00:33:42,715
<i>I think that perhaps I'm not important to him.</i>

545
00:33:42,715 --> 00:33:47,375
<i>That was the reason why I was upset and decided to leave.</i>

546
00:33:47,375 --> 00:33:52,915
<i>What's the point of me regretting it here all alone?</i>

547
00:33:53,585 --> 00:33:55,355
<i>We've now...</i>

548
00:33:57,465 --> 00:34:00,465
<i>drifted apart from each other.</i>

549
00:34:00,465 --> 00:34:05,465
<i>I have no courage to rekindle our relationship now.</i>

550
00:34:14,985 --> 00:34:19,085
<i>Hey, the meals in the canteen today are pretty good.</i>

551
00:34:19,085 --> 00:34:21,455
<i>I got you some as well.</i>

552
00:34:25,675 --> 00:34:27,835
<i>I'm talking to you.</i>

553
00:34:32,955 --> 00:34:37,095
<i>Mr. Luo, do you know</i>

554
00:34:37,095 --> 00:34:41,265
<i>the overseas address of Jin Ning's workplace?</i>

555
00:34:42,735 --> 00:34:44,635
<i>I want to see her.</i>

556
00:34:45,295 --> 00:34:49,705
<i>I've been waiting for this for a year.</i>

557
00:34:53,610 --> 00:34:55,470
<i>[Jing Ning's address]</i>

558
00:34:59,855 --> 00:35:01,005
All right then.

559
00:35:01,005 --> 00:35:04,925
That's the end of my story.

560
00:35:04,925 --> 00:35:06,675
But I think that's just half of the story.

561
00:35:06,675 --> 00:35:08,485
It's less than a half to me.

562
00:35:08,485 --> 00:35:10,355
Why did one leave while the other one let it happen?

563
00:35:10,355 --> 00:35:14,355
Did they finally become a couple after the guy went to look for the lady?

564
00:35:14,355 --> 00:35:18,245
This kid is too good at math and lacks imagination.

565
00:35:18,245 --> 00:35:20,188
Am I right?

566
00:35:23,915 --> 00:35:25,755
Why are you here?

567
00:35:27,265 --> 00:35:31,235
Isn't the story about us?

568
00:35:31,235 --> 00:35:34,225
Who told you that? Cheeky.

569
00:35:39,045 --> 00:35:41,785
Back then, when I brought you back,

570
00:35:41,785 --> 00:35:46,975
I promised to treat you well forever.

571
00:35:52,975 --> 00:35:55,555
Did I make it?

572
00:35:56,525 --> 00:35:58,458
You did.

573
00:35:59,195 --> 00:36:03,525
You did better than what you promised.

574
00:36:15,205 --> 00:36:17,165
I'm sorry.

575
00:36:27,035 --> 00:36:28,435
Mom, I'm leaving now!

576
00:36:28,435 --> 00:36:31,905
Hold on! Why are you in such a rush?

577
00:36:31,905 --> 00:36:33,775
You haven't had the porridge.

578
00:36:33,775 --> 00:36:36,605
I want to rehearse with Zhang Qi. I'm worried that he will run away.

579
00:36:36,605 --> 00:36:38,436
Sunian, hurry up! We're leaving.

580
00:36:38,436 --> 00:36:39,975
Sunian!

581
00:36:39,975 --> 00:36:42,205
It's not ladylike at all when you act like that.

582
00:36:42,205 --> 00:36:43,105
Hurry up!

583
00:36:43,105 --> 00:36:45,285
Sunian. Take the eggs.

584
00:36:45,285 --> 00:36:46,955
I wonder from whom did she inherit that attitude.

585
00:36:46,955 --> 00:36:48,255
I don't like eggs.

586
00:36:48,255 --> 00:36:49,975
It's all right that you didn't take them in the past.

587
00:36:49,975 --> 00:36:51,645
But I cooked them today.

588
00:36:51,645 --> 00:36:54,485
<i>Your cooking skills are worse than my dad's. They might not even be cooked.</i>

589
00:36:54,485 --> 00:36:56,286
- Faster, Sunian.
- See you, Ms. Jin Ning.

590
00:36:56,286 --> 00:36:57,175
- Careful.
- No need to rush.

591
00:36:57,175 --> 00:36:58,808
Bye-bye.

592
00:37:01,205 --> 00:37:04,635
This boy is such a fussy eater.

593
00:37:04,635 --> 00:37:07,255
But he's so tall despite being a fussy eater.

594
00:37:07,255 --> 00:37:10,155
He has better food.

595
00:37:10,155 --> 00:37:13,175
Xue can't grow any taller.

596
00:37:13,895 --> 00:37:15,515
What's that supposed to mean?

597
00:37:15,515 --> 00:37:16,965
She's right.

598
00:37:16,965 --> 00:37:20,165
In my eyes, Xue is just perfect.

599
00:37:21,005 --> 00:37:25,315
In Zheng's eyes, you're perfect as well.

600
00:37:25,315 --> 00:37:26,996
Come on. We're talking about the children.

601
00:37:26,996 --> 00:37:29,385
I've cleaned the bike. Let's go.

602
00:37:29,385 --> 00:37:31,245
I'll raise the rear part. Be careful.

603
00:37:31,245 --> 00:37:33,138
We're leaving.

604
00:37:34,855 --> 00:37:38,288
Look at them. Look at this couple.

605
00:37:40,005 --> 00:37:42,955
We're a pretty nice couple as well.

606
00:37:42,955 --> 00:37:44,895
- Go away.
- Okay.

607
00:37:46,585 --> 00:37:49,296
Whoever leaves last has to lock the door.

608
00:37:50,335 --> 00:37:53,468
Mom, I've got to go.

609
00:37:53,468 --> 00:37:55,208
Hold on!

610
00:37:57,735 --> 00:37:59,475
Give it to Xue.

611
00:37:59,475 --> 00:38:00,585
What is this?

612
00:38:00,585 --> 00:38:01,855
I made her this prop.

613
00:38:01,855 --> 00:38:05,185
She's been working hard on the stage play lately. We should support her.

614
00:38:05,185 --> 00:38:06,875
Don't they look pretty?

615
00:38:08,605 --> 00:38:10,755
It's not like Xue's going to act in the play.

616
00:38:13,530 --> 00:38:15,415
<i>[Teachers' Office]</i>

617
00:38:15,415 --> 00:38:17,665
Tang Ya, listen to me. Please don't be nervous.

618
00:38:17,665 --> 00:38:21,255
I'm most confident that the screenplay, the male lead,

619
00:38:21,255 --> 00:38:24,286
and all the costumes, and props can win over all the judges.

620
00:38:24,286 --> 00:38:26,685
- Good morning, Shiyin.
- My mom asked me to give you this.

